race.comment: SILK SONIC (8) comfortably won her maiden over this distance at the Sunshine Coast two back. Tried 1200m for the first time and failed last start at Eagle Farm. Back in her comfort zone this evening and from the ideal gate should give backers a wonderful sight. VIALE (11) returned from a 28-week break last time out under new trainer Keven Kemp and did a good job to hold on for second over 1100m at Ipswich after leading. Won her maiden when second-up last prep and has placed two from three at today's journey. Nicely placed to play a big role. CHASING TIME (6) has not appeared since recording an all-the-way win on debut over 870m at this track in July. Trialled twice recently and looks set for a positive return. VESPER LYND (10) won her maiden over this trip at Eagle Farm two back but was less effective against Class 1 opposition there last time. Worth another chance. Recent trial winner BLUISH HUE (4) is a major contender back for a second campaign off a 21-week break.
